### DOM Structure for Styling

```html
<div class="northwestern-spatial-layout northwestern-spatial-layout--{viewMode}">
  <!-- Grid container with calculated dimensions -->
  <div class="spatial-grid spatial-grid--{screenSize}" style="grid-template: {calculated}">
    
    <!-- Drug class group boundaries (Agent 3.2) -->
    <div class="group-boundary group-boundary--beta-lactams">
      <div class="group-label">β-Lactams</div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Individual antibiotic positions -->
    <div class="antibiotic-position antibiotic-position--{row}-{col}" data-antibiotic-id="{id}">
      <EnhancedNorthwesternPieChart 
        antibiotic={antibiotic}
        size={gridConfig.chartSize}
        interactive={true}
      />
      <div class="position-label">{antibiotic.name}</div>
    </div>
    
    <!-- Connection lines between related antibiotics (Agent 3.2) -->
    <svg class="connection-overlay">
      <line class="drug-class-connection" />
    </svg>
    
    <!-- Filter highlight overlay (Agent 3.3) -->
    <div class="filter-overlay" style="display: none">
      <div class="highlight-region highlight-region--{filterType}"></div>
    </div>
    
  </div>
  
  <!-- Loading state for virtualization (Agent 3.4) -->
  <div class="spatial-loading" style="display: none">
    <div class="loading-skeleton"></div>
  </div>
  
</div>
```

### Performance Requirements

#### Rendering Targets
- **Initial Layout**: <1000ms for 30 antibiotics
- **Responsive Resize**: <300ms layout recalculation
- **Filter Application**: <200ms highlight updates
- **Group Selection**: <100ms boundary highlights

#### Memory Constraints
- **Grid Calculations**: <10MB memory footprint
- **Position Cache**: <5MB for all breakpoints
- **Virtualization**: Support 100+ antibiotics future expansion

### Medical Accuracy Requirements

#### Northwestern Methodology Compliance
- Spatial groupings must match Northwestern teaching hospital methodology
- Drug class relationships must be clinically accurate
- Antibiotic positioning must support educational workflows
- Coverage patterns must align with clinical decision-making

#### Clinical Workflow Integration
- <30 second emergency access to any antibiotic
- Support rapid drug class comparison
- Enable quick generation comparisons within classes
- Maintain spectrum coverage visibility

